headline: How Recent Policy And Earnings Signals Are Rewriting The Story For Centene (CNC)
summary: The latest update to the Centene stock narrative centers on a refreshed fair value estimate, which now sits at about US$44.18 per share versus about US$41.12 in prior work. This shift reflects analysts trying to balance optimism about long term earnings power in government managed care with ongoing policy, reimbursement and utilization questions that could influence how quickly that potential shows up in the numbers. headline: Deutsche Bank Raises Centene (CNC) PT to $39 While Maintaining Hold Rating
summary: Centene Corporation (NYSE:CNC) is one of the best stocks under $50 to invest in. On February 10, Deutsche Bank raised its price target for Centene from $32 to $39 while keeping a Hold rating on the shares. The firm noted that the shares had previously been caught in a downward trend affecting its industry peers. […]

headline: Wells Fargo Maintains Equal-Weight on Centene, Raises Price Target to $44
summary: Wells Fargo  analyst Stephen Baxter   maintains Centene (NYSE:CNC) with a Equal-Weight and raises the price target from $43 to $44.
